        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Appointed minister to Russia in 1809, John Quincy Adams served until his appointment as secretary of state in 1817. Adams became a member of the American Philosophical Society in 1818 and was elected the 6th President of the United States in 1825. He served one term.</p>
        </bioghist>
